## Phase 10: Install ArgoCD

### 10.1 — Install ArgoCD via Helm
```bash
helm repo add argo https://argoproj.github.io/argo-helm
helm repo update

helm upgrade --install argocd argo/argo-cd \
  --namespace argocd \
  --set server.service.type=LoadBalancer \
  --set configs.params."server\.insecure"=true \
  --wait --timeout 5m

kubectl get pods -n argocd
```
📸 **Screenshot**: ArgoCD pods running

### 10.2 — Get ArgoCD Credentials
```bash
ARGOCD_PASS=$(kubectl get secret argocd-initial-admin-secret \
  -n argocd -o jsonpath="{.data.password}" | base64 --decode)

ARGOCD_LB=$(kubectl get svc argocd-server -n argocd \
  -o jsonpath='{.status.loadBalancer.ingress[0].hostname}')

echo "============================================"
echo "  ArgoCD Access"
echo "============================================"
echo "  URL:      http://$ARGOCD_LB"
echo "  Username: admin"
echo "  Password: $ARGOCD_PASS"
echo "============================================"
```
📸 **Screenshot**: ArgoCD credentials

### 10.3 — Open ArgoCD UI
Open `http://<ARGOCD_LB>` in your browser and login.
📸 **Screenshot**: ArgoCD login page + empty dashboard

---

## Phase 11: Bootstrap ArgoCD (App-of-Apps)

### 11.1 — Register CD Repo with ArgoCD
```bash
argocd login $ARGOCD_LB --username admin --password "$ARGOCD_PASS" --insecure

argocd repo add "https://github.com/Deloitte-DT-Training/HU-DevOps-Lokesk-26-CD.git" \
  --username "x-access-token" \
  --password "$CD_REPO_TOKEN" \
  --insecure-skip-server-verification

echo "✅ CD repo registered"
```

### 11.2 — Apply App-of-Apps
```bash
kubectl apply -f ~/cd-repo/argocd-apps/app-of-apps.yaml
echo "✅ App-of-Apps applied — ArgoCD is now managing everything!"
```

### 11.3 — Verify ArgoCD Applications
```bash
sleep 30
argocd app list
```
📸 **Screenshot**: All apps in ArgoCD showing Synced/Healthy

---

## Phase 12: Full Verification

### 12.1 — All Pods Summary
```bash
echo "============================================"
echo "  SU DevOps Platform — EKS Deployment"
echo "============================================"
kubectl get pods -A | grep -v kube-system
echo ""
kubectl get pods -A --no-headers | wc -l
echo "total pods running"
```
📸 **Screenshot**: All pods across all namespaces

### 12.2 — All Services Summary
```bash
kubectl get svc -A | grep -v kube-system
```
📸 **Screenshot**: All services with their types and ports

### 12.3 — Node Utilization
```bash
kubectl top nodes 2>/dev/null || echo "Metrics server loading..."
kubectl get nodes -o custom-columns=NAME:.metadata.name,PODS:.status.capacity.pods
for node in $(kubectl get nodes -o jsonpath='{.items[*].metadata.name}'); do
  echo -n "$node: "
  kubectl get pods -A --field-selector spec.nodeName=$node --no-headers | wc -l
done
```
📸 **Screenshot**: Node pod counts (should be well under limits now)

### 12.4 — Final Test: End-to-End API
```bash
KONG_LB=$(kubectl get svc kong-gateway-proxy -n api-gateway \
  -o jsonpath='{.status.loadBalancer.ingress[0].hostname}')

echo "🌐 Frontend:     http://$KONG_LB/"
echo "👤 Users API:    http://$KONG_LB/api/users"
echo "📦 Products API: http://$KONG_LB/api/products"
echo "🛒 Orders API:   http://$KONG_LB/api/orders"
echo ""
echo "Testing all endpoints..."
for EP in "/" "/api/users" "/api/products" "/api/orders"; do
  STATUS=$(curl -s -o /dev/null -w "%{http_code}" http://$KONG_LB$EP)
  echo "  $EP → HTTP $STATUS"
done
```
📸 **Screenshot**: All endpoints returning HTTP 200

